  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div xml:id="KT218-kilavi">
        <p type="edition">piriviṭai āṟṟāḷ eṉak kavaṉṟa tōḻikkuk kiḻatti uraittatu. </p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">Told by HER to the confidante who was anxious she would
          not have the strength in the time of separation. </p>
      </div>

      <div xml:id="KT218">
        <lg type="edition">

          <l>viṭarmukai yaṭukkattu viṟalkeḻu cūlikkuk</l>
          <l>kaṭaṉum pūṇāṅ kainnūl yāvām</l>
          <l>puḷḷu mōrām viricciyu nillā</l>
          <l>muḷḷalu muḷḷā maṉṟē tōḻi</l>
          <l>yuyirkkuyi raṉṉa rākaliṟ ṟammiṉ</l>
          <l>ṟimaippuvarai yamaiyā namvayiṉ</l>
          <l>maṟantāṇ ṭamaital valliyōr māṭṭē.</l>
        </lg>

        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">

          <l rend="indent2">To the victorious Cūli at the mountainside with clefts [and] caves<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">viṭarmukai </term> can also be read as a synonym
            compound, in which case it might convey plurality: many caves.</note></l>
          <l>we don't take up duty [and] don't bind the thread on [our] hand <note place="foot">On
            nūl the -um is missing; better is the variant <term xml:lang="ta">puṇātu</term> ("not
            taking up duty we don't bind the thread ... "). In this case the religious duty would
            consist of binding a thread, whatever that may mean – T.V.G. explains it as a turmeric
            thread worn on the left hand by women, on the right by men, during <term xml:lang="ta">
            pūjā</term> .</note></l>
          <l>and we don't know about omens and we don't depend</l>
          <l rend="indent7">on overheard voices</l>
          <l>and [still] it is not that we don't think and think,<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">uḷḷalum uḷḷām aṉṟē</term> : this is presumably a figura etymologica
            with intensifying sense.</note> friend,</l>
          <l rend="indent3">about him who was able to be content there, having forgotten</l>
          <l rend="indent4">us who have not been content for the blink [of an eye]</l>
          <l rend="indent5">without him, because he [is] life for [our] life.</l>


        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
  </text>
